transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, this is Richard Gresser.

Speaker 1: I asked for another medication, a different medication I think.

Speaker 2: And I've delivered some sodanophyl, AGB.

Speaker 1: I'd like to take a look to see what's going on with your order.

Speaker 2: What's your zip code?

Speaker 1: 60015.

Speaker 2: All right, so I pulled out your zip code.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, what's your first name?

Speaker 2: Richard.

Speaker 1: And last name's Gresser?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 2: So I see that they sent you a new order, sir.

Speaker 1: What does the marking on the new order say on there?

Speaker 2: It says, sodanophyl, 100 milligram tablet.

Speaker 1: One more time, sir, the marking on the pill.

Speaker 2: The marking on the pill is 100.

Speaker 1: Got it. That's going to be the AGB, sir.

Speaker 2: The one that you got previously was the wrong one.

Speaker 1: That was the generic one that said AC on there and a series of numbers.

Speaker 2: The second one you receive is going to be the AGB Viagra.

Speaker 1: Because it has 100 marked on there.

Speaker 2: But I thought, I asked, you have a couple of others.

Speaker 1: I asked for one that will last for up to 14 hours.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it does.

Speaker 1: It lasts up to 14 hours and it works as fast as 15 minutes.

Speaker 2: However, on the label, it won't say that because the doctor can't verify

Speaker 1: that everybody's body's composition is the same.

Speaker 2: However, the pill that you received was the AGB Viagra.

Speaker 1: Okay. Now, please tell me a little bit about the subscription that I have.

Speaker 2: Yeah, right now you have it frozen out.

Speaker 1: It looks like for half the year.

Speaker 2: That way you could just try these out, see how well you like these,

Speaker 1: and then you can call us back once you make a final choice on it to see if you want to keep it.

Speaker 2: Okay. Now, is there any charge for this?

Speaker 1: No, that was free.

Speaker 2: Is there any charge for renewing the prescription?

Speaker 1: Well, yeah.

Speaker 2: I mean, if you're going to get another order, you have to pay for it.

Speaker 1: This one is free because they made a mistake on your first order.

Speaker 2: I got you.

Speaker 1: Now, what will the charge be on the, if I decide to?

Speaker 2: You have a promotion rate of $63.95, sir.

Speaker 1: $63.95?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: And that's for how many?

Speaker 2: Ten pills, what you received right now.

Speaker 1: Well, it's not understood, so I'll get this fixed for you, sir.

Speaker 2: I do apologize.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thanks for your time.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Have a good one.

Speaker 1: Bye.
